**Reduce Function Call Overhead**

1. Use caching mechanisms (e.g., memoization) to store and reuse computed values.
2. Minimize the number of function calls by reducing nesting or using loop-based approaches.

Example:
```javascript
// Before
function fibonacci(n) {
  if (n <= 1) return n;
  return fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2);
}

// After caching and loop optimization
const fibCache = new Map();
function fibonacci(n) {
  if (!fibCache.has(n)) {
    const result = fib(n - 1) + fib(n - 2);
    fibCache.set(n, result);
  }
  return fibCache.get(n);
}
